25/01/2009
PRAGUE, the Czech Republic/ROME, Italy -- Serbia's Deputy Prime Minister Bozidar Djelic said on Friday (January 23rd) his country is planning to formally apply for EU membership in the first half of this year. Djelic met with his Czech counterpart Alexandr Vondra in Prague to discuss Serbia's application during the current Czech EU presidency. Vondra welcomed Belgrade's "ambitious plans", though he cautioned it would take years before Serbia could join. Praising the country's progress, he said the Czech Republic regards Serbia as a "gateway to stability" in the western Balkans.
